Habitat. Mixed conifer forests. Males call from dense understory vegetation and from pine needle litter, most commonly 15 cm or less from the ground but occasionally as high as 3 m above the ground in conifers. This species is associated with mountain misery (
Chamaebatia foliosa Benth.
), incense cedar (
Calocedrus decurrens (Torr.) Florin
), western bracken fern (
Pteridium aquilinum
(L.) Kuhn), and white fir (
Abies concolor (Gord. & Glend.) Lindl. ex Hildebr.
).
